# Justification: cppcheck+misra addon cannot resolve C++ enum types (Result,
# EntryState, ReliabilityClass, MessageType, etc.) without a compile_commands.json.
# These are false-positive "incomplete misra check" warnings, not real violations.
# A compile_commands.json would eliminate them; generating one requires CMake or Bear.
# Deviation: misra-config informational -- not a code defect. Pre-existing limitation.
misra-config

# Justification: noConstructor -- these classes deliberately use an explicit init()
# pattern instead of constructors, following the F-Prime / MISRA recommendation for
# explicit initialization phases with no implicit side effects.
# Deviation: MISRA C++:2023 advisory -- init() pattern preferred over constructors for
# safety-critical embedded code where initialization order and error handling matter.
noConstructor

